  "content": "indows</div>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill\" style=\"width: 78%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ef4444, #dc2626);\">\n          2.2 &ndash; 5.0+ GB\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"divider\"></div>\n  <div class=\"stat-grid\">\n    <div class=\"stat-box\">\n      <div class=\"stat-value highlight-green\">1 GB</div>\n      <div class=\"stat-label\">Ubuntu idle usage<br>Modular kernel, minimal services</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat-box\">\n      <div class=\"stat-value highlight-red\">5 GB+</div>\n      <div class=\"stat-label\">Windows 11 idle usage<br>SysMain, telemetry, caching</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat-box\">\n      <div class=\"stat-value highlight-amber\">~4 GB</div>\n      <div class=\"stat-label\">macOS idle usage<br>Pre-caching & frameworks</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat-box\">\n      <div class=\"stat-value highlight-cyan\">2&ndash;5x</div>\n      <div class=\"stat-label\">Linux is 2&ndash;5x more efficient<br>depending on config &amp; total RAM</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">03 / 08</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SLIDE 4: WINDOWS vs WSL vs NATIVE LINUX         -->\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Real Comparison</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    Windows vs WSL vs<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-cyan\">Native Linux</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\n    I needed Docker for VS Code Devcontainers. Here's the cost of each path.\n  </div>",
